<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1651,2001]" box="[151,288,1651,1677]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1651,2001]" box="[198,974,1691,1717]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
Male (
<figureCitation box="[274,387,1691,1717]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 2" captionStartId="2.[151,269,701,725]" captionTargetBox="[154,1436,181,675]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[154,1451,177,675]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 2. Idmon flavata sp. nov. (Scale = 10 mm) 1. Dorasal view, 2. Ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273822/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
Figs. 
<number box="[341,387,1691,1717]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Forewing length 
<quantity box="[609,694,1691,1717]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" unit="mm" value="17.0">17 mm</quantity>
, antenna length 
<quantity box="[885,969,1691,1717]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" unit="mm" value="11.0">11 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1651,2001]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
Antennae dark brown, longer than 
<number box="[567,577,1731,1757]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[588,604,1731,1757]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="2.0">2</number>
of forewing costa, club yellow ventrally; palpi second segment erect, densely covered with long greyish white scales ventrally, third segment long and slender, distinctly protruding.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1651,2001]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
Wings upper surface with ground color dark brown, unmarked, cilia grey, without secondary sexual characters. Forewing underside ground color the same as that of upper surface, covered with yellow scales at apex and the end of cell. Hindwing underside yellow, costa and termen brown, veins yellow, with small black spots in the spaces Cu 
<number box="[342,350,1987,2001]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="2.0">2</number>
to Rs, the one in space Sc+R 
<number box="[694,702,1987,2001]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" value="1.0">1</number>
blurred.
</paragraph>
<caption box="[151,1106,701,725]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273822/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" targetBox="[154,1436,181,675]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1106,701,725]" box="[151,1106,701,725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,322,701,725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">FIGURES 1–2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[329,478,702,725]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Idmon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[329,478,702,725]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Idmon flavata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[485,567,702,725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(Scale = 10 mm) 1. Dorasal view, 2. Ventral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,777,1043]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[385,501,777,803]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1741,1765]" captionTargetBox="[248,1311,1189,1694]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[232,1355,1142,1715]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 7. Male genitalia of Idmon flavata sp. nov. 3. ring, lateral view, 4. tegumen, dorsal view, 5. valva, inner view, 6. aedeagus, 7. juxta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273823/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
Figs. 
<number box="[453,501,777,803]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="5.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="3.0">3–7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Uncus long, about twice longer than tegumen, deeply bifid at half distal portion, its two arms long and thin, running slightly outwardly; socius absent; gnathos well developed, elbowshaped, membranous and separated each other at tip; saccus rather long; valva simple, broad, with the distal upper portion shallowly bifid, forming the ampullar and the harpal processes, the ampullar process with upper margin slightly swelled, the harpal process with lower margin obviously convex, outer margin arched; aedeagus with subzonal sheath nearly as long as suprazonal sheath, and bifurcated distally; juxta U-shaped with lateral arms curved inwardly.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273823/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" targetBox="[248,1311,1189,1694]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1741,1799]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,325,1741,1765]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">FIGURES 3–7.</emphasis>
Male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[527,678,1742,1765]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Idmon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[527,678,1742,1765]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Idmon flavata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[686,771,1741,1764]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
3. ring, lateral view, 4. tegumen, dorsal view, 5. valva, inner view, 6. aedeagus, 7. juxta.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1851,2001]" box="[151,244,1851,1877]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Remark</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1851,2001]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,152,218]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="60" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
The new species strikingly resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Chou &amp; Huang, 1994" authorityName="Chou &amp; Huang" authorityYear="1994" box="[652,1137,1891,1917]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Idmon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fujianana">
<emphasis box="[652,848,1891,1916]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Idmon fujianana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Chou" box="[865,1128,1891,1917]" pageId="2" pageNumber="62" refString="Chou, I. (ed.) (1994) Monographia Rhopalocerorum Sinensium. Henan Scientific and Technological Publishing House, Zhengzhou, 854 pp." type="book" year="1994">
Chou &amp; Huang, 
<number box="[1066,1128,1891,1917]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="1994.0">1994</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but can be easily distinguished by hindwing underside densely covered with yellow scales, as well as the clearly defined small black spots in spaces Cu 
<number box="[368,376,1987,2001]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="2.0">2</number>
to Rs, the one in space Sc+R 
<number box="[725,733,1987,2001]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="1.0">1</number>
indistinct; uncus with the two lateral arms not parallel each other; valva with the ampullar and harpal processes hardly connected at apex; juxta U-shaped with lateral arm curved inwardly.
</paragraph>
